            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This seems like the result of `:!` not having a default value for the `{program}` arg (like `=` does with `'equalprg'`). Perhaps a good implementation of this would add a buffer local option that can be used as the default value of `{program}` for `!`, globally defaulting to the user shell (if found)?\n",
